cs.CC, cs.AI, cs.GT, cs.DS, cs.LG. 

The paper deals with the computational complexity of playing Magic: the Gathering optimally, which falls under the category of computational complexity (cs.CC). The authors use techniques from artificial intelligence (cs.AI) to analyze the game, and graph theory (cs.GT) to model it. They also use data structures (cs.DS) to represent the game state and machine learning (cs.LG) to train agents to play the game.
